  "markup": "In the April webinar we will discuss how to read peer-reviewed research papers with a critical eye, and how to glean practical take-home data from these often confusing and complicated publications.\u003Cbr /\u003E\n\u003Cbr /\u003E\nEducating the listener on critically reading peer-reviewed research will be the focus.\u0026nbsp; Teaching the difference between various types of research such as RTC,Double and Triple blinded studies, and better equip the listener to cut through the fog of information.\u003Cbr /\u003E\n\u003Cbr /\u003E\nJoin Dr. Chris Carraway and special guest Timothy Demchak, PhD for a very informative review of what can be a very confusing topic."
}]]></Value>
